# Flipkart Sales Dashboard — Setup Guide

## Folder Structure
```
flipkart_dashboard/
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt
├── .streamlit/
│   └── secrets.toml          ← you create this (see below)
└── .gitignore
```

---

## Step 1: Install Python packages
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Step 2: Set up Google Sheets as Database

### A. Create a Google Cloud Project
1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
2. Create a new project (e.g. "Flipkart Dashboard")
3. Enable these two APIs:
   - **Google Sheets API**
   - **Google Drive API**

### B. Create a Service Account
1. Go to **IAM & Admin → Service Accounts**
2. Click **Create Service Account**
3. Give it a name (e.g. `flipkart-dashboard`)
4. Click **Create and Continue**
5. Skip role assignment → click **Done**
6. Click on the service account → **Keys tab** → **Add Key → JSON**
7. Download the JSON file

### C. Configure secrets.toml
Create `.streamlit/secrets.toml` in your project folder and paste the contents from the downloaded JSON:

```toml
[gcp_service_account]
type = "service_account"
project_id = "your-project-id"
private_key_id = "abc123..."
private_key = "-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
client_email = "flipkart-dashboard@your-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
client_id = "123456789"
auth_uri = "https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth"
token_uri = "https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token"
auth_provider_x509_cert_url = "https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v1/certs"
client_x509_cert_url = "https://www.googleapis.com/robot/v1/..."
universe_domain = "googleapis.com"
```

### D. Share the Google Sheet with Service Account
The app auto-creates the sheet and shares it with the service account.  
If you get permission errors, manually share the sheet with the `client_email` address above and give it **Editor** access.

---

## Step 3: Run the Dashboard
```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

---

## Daily Workflow
1. Download the **Earn More Report** from Flipkart Seller Hub
2. Open the dashboard → sidebar → Upload file
3. Click **"Save to Google Sheets"**
4. Dashboard auto-updates with new data

---

## Features
| Feature | Details |
|---|---|
| **Daily Upload** | Upload any Flipkart Earn More XLSX — deduplication prevents double-counting |
| **Google Sheets DB** | All data stored in Google Sheets, accessible anywhere |
| **Brand Filter** | Filter all views by brand |
| **Overview** | Today's sale/cancel/return KPIs with DoD comparison |
| **DoD Analysis** | Day-on-Day charts and % change table |
| **WoW Analysis** | Week-on-Week charts and % change table |
| **MoM Analysis** | Month-on-Month (auto-activates when 2+ months of data present) |
| **Declining SKUs** | Top SKUs losing GMV WoW — ready for action |
| **Action Points** | AI-style dynamic recommendations based on your data |

---

